However, 3 weeks before the end of college, we were informed that the GPUs in the servers at CCBD were not working, and were asked to do a class project. All four of us were in the Big Data course. Two of us have got A grades in Big Data.

The Centre for Cloud Computing and Big Data (CCBD) is one of the leading research organizations at PES University.  It’s recent accomplishments in the field of Big Data Technologies and Cloud technologies have only enhanced its credentials.

We are a group of determined individuals who are highly interested in working on a CCBD project. We are committed towards the project and are sure that we will deliver a sizeable research output. 

The CGPA details (at the end of five semesters) of the team members are listed below:
Pradyumna YM - 9.97

Our academic credentials show that we have the capability to sustain under pressure and deliver results in projects, while also dealing with academics. 

Our team has experience in working under the fields of machine learning, data analytics, web technologies and database technologies and are keen on using our existing knowledge to enhance the quality of work performed on the project. Further, we have participated in various research internships in the previous summer break and are thus familiar with working in a research environment and dealing with hard deadlines.
